                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>By an exchange of notes dated November 26 and December 12, 1951, at Managua, the
                    United States and Nicaragua concluded an agreement, which entered into force on
                    the latter date, providing for the free movement of military aircraft of each
                    country through the airspace of the other. The notes were transmitted to the
                    Department of <pb facs="1549" n="1527" xml:id="pg_1527"/> State under cover of
                    despatch 450, from Managua, December 19, 1951, not printed (611.1794/12–1951).
                    For text, see <gloss target="#t_TIAS1">TIAS</gloss> No. 2460, or 3 <gloss
                        target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> (pt. 2) 2863.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
